cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper proposes a framework for annotating diachronic changes in lexical meaning, which is relevant to computational models of lexical semantic change. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning and annotation, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses relatedness and semantic changes, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
